metadata.name: Alchemy #22
metadata.description:
Alchemy (or Maria Paritura) is a generative art project (p5js) based on Kandinsky's thoughts -Corcerning the Spiritual in Art-  about reducing artistic expression to his essentials. 

Inspired on a medieval painting of the Virgin pregnant with the sun. 
Shape has been removed and it has been synthesized into its primarial colours: blue, red and yellow. As soon as the figurative image is taken out, the symbolism comes out clearly. The union of heaven and earth reveals the Phylosopher's Stone. A sunrise where the Above finds the Below (As above so below, Esmerald Table). 

LVI (56) editions. 

Created by @mehno_art.

metadata.name: Kings of Babylon #156
metadata.description:
Excavate Kings from the past.
Some are born first, and some are born later.
The long-dead are no longer breathless.
The new kings hail from distant dimensions.
Hunt their crowns, peel their eyes and savor in their glory.

metadata.name: Kitty's Frame #2
metadata.description:
"Kitty's Frame", by NJT

"Kitty's Frame" is a digital-hand-drawing collection that can Randomly Generate.

"Kitty's Frame" contains Traits 40 (152 layers), and it can make your own unique NFT.

These NFTs are randomly minted, which is a chance for everyone to get a rare version.

metadata.name: Flower Arrangement #5
metadata.description:
Flower arrangement made by code.

Possible features:
- Style: Natural, Oval, Triangular, Grassy
- Orientation: Square, Portrait, Landscape
- Palette: White, Cream, Tan, Pink, Green, Blue, Yellow, Orange
- Primary flower: Mix, Gerbera, Gerbera 2, Dahlia, Dahlia 2, Spiky, Unknown
- Primary color: Random, Light, Dark
- Secondary color: Random, Light, Dark
- Vase shape: Cylinder, Tumbler, Round, Curve
- Dish: true, false
- Table: true, false
- Texture: true, false

Live view options:
- Press "s" key: Saves the high resolution image (3300 x 3300 for square, 4200 x 3300 for portrait, 3300 x 4200 for landscape)

Depending on the device you run it on, it may take some time for the drawing to complete.
Best viewed in larger window size.
Made with p5js.

August 2022
ykxotkx

metadata.name: =DMT= #31
metadata.description:
The Spirit Molecule, an experience out of this world, available in this world.

What will you see when you take your =DMT=? I wish you a great trip.

Groups of color palettes, lines and bezier curves combine to create what sometimes looks like a sun, an eye, a flower, an explosion, a pair of wings or a combination of these.

I hope in the future Psychedelics will be accessible to people in controlled settings with professional care and support. 
The Ayahuasca ceremonies happening around the world are a good step in this direction.

Press 's' to save a 3000x3000 px PNG.

Created by UpOnlyFan in August 2022 with p5js.

metadata.name: Wall of Chart #16
Murmuration #57
metadata.description: A "murmuration" describes both a swarm of starlings, as well as a low continuous sound. This piece reflects on both phenomena, and uses sound waves as the point of origin for the visual interpretation. The non-repetitive nature of the overlapping oscillations form the basis of a potentially endless experience. Four pre-synthesized waveforms spread across the soundstage have been arranged to highlight the emotional quality of the selected mode. Developed as part of the Forefront Web3 Creator Residency

metadata.name: Threads of destiny #109
metadata.description:
"Threads of destiny" is an abstract artwork focusing on the composition and color of elements. Each thread consists of a sequence of shapes that are placed together in a harmonious rhythm, just like our world where each of us, while being unique, together form a larger design, each of the shapes, on the threads of destiny, with the help of each other, make a larger and harmonious composition. 

Various sizes and densities and more than 12 color palettes have been used.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

metadata.name: MONOLITH #202
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

this work is done only with code, using threejs and p5js
it might be a bit slow on low-end devices, be patient
